# Waxing metal

Waxing metal is a technique to **polish** it and **clean off** [oxidation](../../chemistry/oxidation.md) on the surface. A layer of wax can also **slow new oxidation** by limiting water and air at the metal—helpful where you want a durable, low-effort finish outdoors.

**Collinite** wax **Metal 850** (from the marine industry) is quite a good product. I have used it to clean up my stainless steel fence.

